      Does fine-tuning help on Swiss data protection?
    </h1>
    <p class="mt-6 max-w-2xl text-lg prose-muted md:text-xl">
      Not an opinion — a measurement. We took Apertus-8B and ran the same four-way ablation we run at the start of every <a class="link-underline" href="/concepts/evaluation/">Pilot</a>, on a task where the answer can be scored exactly: answering questions about the revised Swiss Data Protection Act with a citation to the exact article it rests on — <em>with</em> a citation to the exact article it rests on. The result: fine-tuning plus retrieval takes the production bar from 37.0% to 54.3%.
    </p>
