<section class="container-x py-20 md:py-28">
  {{ sectionHead("Update · Third iteration (v3)", "Grammar decoding: most of the gain, no training.", "Constraining output to the two-line contract forces any model to emit a parseable answer + citation.") }}
  <p class="mt-6 max-w-3xl prose-muted">Much of what the fine-tune was buying turns out to be <em>output format</em>. Forcing the two-line contract with a formal grammar — <strong class="text-ink-700 dark:text-ink-300">zero training</strong> — recovers most of it, and separates it from what the model genuinely learned.</p>
